info.smart_tools.smartactors.core.message_processing

Interface IMessageProcessor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MessageProcessor

    public interface IMessageProcessor
    Interface for a object responding for processing of a single message.

    • Method Detail

      • getMessage

        IObject getMessage()
        Returns the message object.
        Returns:
        the message being processed

      • getContext

        IObject getContext()
        Returns the context object of the message being processed. Context contains all the non-serializable data related to the message.
        Returns:
        the context of message processing

      • getResponse

        IObject getResponse()
        Returns the response object being formed for the processed message. The response object will be sent to the sender of the message being processed (and may be serialized in process of sending) so should contain only serializable data.
        Returns:
        the response for the message

      • getSequence

        IMessageProcessingSequence getSequence()
        Returns the IMessageProcessingSequence managing order of receivers receiving this message.
        Returns:
        the sequence of receivers that should receive the message

      • getEnvironment

        IObject getEnvironment()
        Returns the message environment object. The environment object should contain at least the following fields: - "message" - the message itself (as instance of IObject) - "context" - the IObject containing non-serializable objects related to processing of the message - "response" - the IObject containing fields that will be sent as a response to the processed message - "sequence" - the IMessageProcessingSequence instance associated with the message - "arguments" - the arguments IObject passed from IReceiverChain
        Returns:
        the environment object

      • setConfig

        void setConfig(IObject config)
        throws InvalidArgumentException
        Set a global configuration object to use for processing of next message.
        Parameters:
        config - the configuration object
        Throws:
        InvalidArgumentException - if config is null

      • process

        void process(IObject message,
             IObject context)
      throws InvalidArgumentException,
             ResolutionException,
             ChangeValueException
        Start processing new message using this instance of IMessageProcessor.
        Parameters:
        message - the message to process
        context - the context of message processing
        Throws:
        InvalidArgumentException - if message is null
        InvalidArgumentException - if context is null
        ResolutionException - if fails to resolve any dependency
        ChangeValueException - if modification of internal environment object fails

      • pauseProcess

        void pauseProcess()
           throws AsynchronousOperationException
        Notify this message processor that currently called message receiver started a asynchronous operation and the processor should not call any following receivers until it is completed.
        Throws:
        AsynchronousOperationException - if called outside of IMessageReceiver.receive(info.smart_tools.smartactors.core.message_processing.IMessageProcessor) call after completion of all asynchronous operations

      • continueProcess

        void continueProcess(Throwable e)
              throws AsynchronousOperationException
        Notify this message processor that a asynchronous operation (on start of which the message processor was notified by call of pauseProcess()) is completed.
        Parameters:
        e - the exception occurred during asynchronous operation or null if operation completed successful
        Throws:
        AsynchronousOperationException - if all asynchronous operations are already completed i.e. number of calls to #continueProcess is greater than number of calls to pauseProcess() since start of execution of last receiver
